#cinemaxpartner Like a lot of people, I was a huge Bruce Lee fan as a kid. I would watch his movies with incessant fascination and awe, secretly hoping I could pick up on some martial arts techniques. Of course, I never did learn how to use nunchucks or fend off 5 people at a time, but the pure elation I’d get from watching Bruce Lee doing his thing was inspiring. You can imagine how excited I was to hear that I get to work with @Cinemax to create a cocktail inspired by the show based on Bruce Lee’s writings, Warrior! The cocktail is formatted after mid 1800’s style punch recipes, so it’s a perfect balance of sweet, sour, bitter, spice, and spirit. Happy mixing! Cheers! 

Be sure to catch the season finale of Warrior this Friday, December 4 on Cinemax! #warriormax

One Inch Punch
30ml (1oz) Cognac
30ml (1oz) Gin
20ml (.75oz) Pineapple Juice
15ml (.5oz) Lemon Juice
15ml (.5oz) Green Tea Cordial*
3dsh Angustora Bitters

*Green Tea Cordial
Steep 5 tea bags in 10 oz of hot water for 10 minutes. Discard tea bags, measure out 100ml of tea and 100g of cane sugar. Combine the tea and sugar, in a microwave safe glass, and microwave for 45 seconds. Carefully remove from microwave and stir until sugar and tea are combined.

#JasonFYu

node.text:
Honestly, I’m not sure how today isn’t National Mint Julep Day. Anyway, it’s the Kentucky Derby today, and of course, the cocktail of choice is the famed Mint Julep. It’s refreshing, it’s bright, and it’s an absolute classic. However, just for fun, I’m going extra old school with this recipe, and though it’s not a new idea, I’m adding just a little extra flavor to this one. Happy Derby day, all, and cheers!

I Do Declare... (Strawberry Mint Julep)
60ml @argonautbrandy Saloon St.
15ml Strawberry syrup (to taste)
6 Mint Leaves
5drp Saline
Strawberry dust

#kentuckyderby #mintjulep #julep #classiccocktails #brandy #cocktails #cocktailsofinstagram #drinkstagram #instadrink #imbibe #thirsty #liqpic #JasonFYu #losangeles

node.text:
Hey everyone! In light of the current violence against the Asian American community, a few friends of mine and I are trying to raise money for the @hateisavirus organization. With your donation, you will receive your choice of one of 10 different cocktails created by myself and nine other viciously talented LA-based AAPI bartenders.
The money received will be distributed to local and national organizations addressing long and short term goals that will help uplift the AAPI community. For example, programs related to mental health, better protections for our elderly, AAPI representation, solidarity-building, and the list goes on.
Initially dedicated to my mother, and now, to everyone in the community. A little love goes a long way. Cheers!

Roses From Kathy (V)
Haku Vodka, European rose, Vanilla foam, lemon & lime.
